Locate the "build" script.

Ensure it ONLY calls next build and does not include any Hardhat, deployment, or compilation commands (hardhat compile, npx hardhat run, etc.).

Script Type	Example Code (Likely Problem)	Correct Code (The Fix)
"build"	"hardhat compile && next build"	"next build"
Commit this one-line change to your GitHub repository. When Vercel re-runs the build, it will only execute the front-end rendering process, allowing your public site to go live instantly, securing the final step of the LLAL Protocol.
